      • getLogRecordNotLessThanTxId

        public static com.twitter.util.Future<com.google.common.base.Optional<LogRecordWithDLSN>> getLogRecordNotLessThanTxId(String logName,
                                                                                                                      LogSegmentMetadata segment,
                                                                                                                      long transactionId,
                                                                                                                      ExecutorService executorService,
                                                                                                                      LogSegmentEntryStore entryStore,
                                                                                                                      int nWays)
        Get the log record whose transaction id is not less than provided transactionId.

        It uses a binary-search like algorithm to find the log record whose transaction id is not less than provided transactionId within a log segment. You could think of a log segment in terms of a sequence of records whose transaction ids are non-decreasing. - The sequence of records within a log segment is divided into N pieces. - Find the piece of records that contains a record whose transaction id is not less than provided transactionId. N could be chosen based on trading off concurrency and latency.

        Parameters:
        logName - name of the log
        segment - metadata of the log segment
        transactionId - transaction id
        executorService - executor service used for processing entries
        entryStore - log segment entry store
        nWays - how many number of entries to search in parallel
        Returns:
        found log record. none if all transaction ids are less than provided transactionId.
